---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="About Wilson Tay (Fingerless Coder): a multimedia computing student blending code, design, and cross-disciplinary curiosity."
  currentPage="/about/"
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 md:gap-12 mb-16">
      <img src="/profile.png" alt="Profile"
        class="w-40 h-40 md:w-48 md:h-48 rounded-full shadow-2xl border-4 border-teal-400 object-cover flex-shrink-0 animate-scale-in glow-teal" />
      <div
        class="glass rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10 shadow-2xl backdrop-blur-xl flex-1 w-full relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-400/5 via-transparent to-indigo-400/5"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10">
          <h1
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 text-gradient-teal">
            About Me</h1>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-200 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Multimedia Computing student. Not quite computer science, not quite design.</p>
          <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">Somewhere in between. I write code that works, even if it is not "market-standard". I prefer understanding why over memorizing how.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="space-y-16">
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gradient-coral mb-4">The Technical Side</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-200 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-lg">My friends describe me as "the technical one" in our group. I am not a hardcore computer science person — no, I cannot recite algorithm proofs from memory. But I understand concepts. I know when to use a database, why API limits exist, and how to debug something I did not write.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">Frontend interests me more than I expected. After swapping roles with a teammate in my final year project, I discovered that building interfaces is actually satisfying — when you have a clear direction.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gradient-teal mb-4">The Non-Technical Side</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-200 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-lg">Friends call me "human dictionary" or "human Wikipedia". I remember random facts. Philosophy, history, politics, economics, law, society — if it is not in the standard curriculum, I have probably read about it.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">I like exploring ideas across disciplines. Why do societies organize the way they do? What makes music evoke emotions? How do different cultures approach the same problem?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gradient-coral mb-4">Interests</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-teal-400">Culture & Media</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">K-pop (Twice, Itzy, IVE, Le Sserafim, aespa, NMIXX, BABYMONSTER), film, and whatever catches my attention on YouTube.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-indigo-400">Music</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">I do not "know" music technically. I listen to feel it, and through repetition, I figure it out myself. Ryuichi Sakamoto is a constant presence.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-coral-400">Self-Research</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Philosophy, history, and various "-isms". I like building my own understanding from multiple sources rather than accepting single narratives.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-teal-400">Games</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Games that make you think. Not necessarily complex, but with interesting mechanics or narratives worth discussing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gradient-teal mb-4">Academic Direction</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-200 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-lg">I am considering further studies. Not because I want to escape work, but because I genuinely enjoy learning. Understanding systems deeply appeals to me more than rapid industry iteration.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">The multimedia computing course has given me a broad foundation. I am still figuring out where I want to specialize, but I know I want to keep asking "why" rather than just "how".</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gradient-coral mb-6">Technologies</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <span class="chip">Java</span>
          <span class="chip">PHP</span>
          <span class="chip">JavaScript</span>
          <span class="chip">Python</span>
          <span class="chip">C#</span>
          <span class="chip">HTML5</span>
          <span class="chip">CSS3</span>
          <span class="chip">Tailwind CSS</span>
          <span class="chip">React</span>
          <span class="chip">Node.js</span>
          <span class="chip">MySQL</span>
          <span class="chip">MongoDB</span>
          <span class="chip">Git</span>
          <span class="chip">GitHub</span>
          <span class="chip">Docker</span>
          <span class="chip">REST APIs</span>
          <span class="chip">Phaser3</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gradient-teal mb-4">Get In Touch</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 text-lg">If you want to discuss projects, ideas, or just have a conversation, feel free to reach out.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          Contact Me
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="card text-center mt-8 opacity-60">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 italic">
          AI can help you do everything? Why don't you use AI dev yourself?
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
